Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish. Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Saute onions until tender. Transfer to prepared dish and top with crushed potato chips. Dissolve bouillon in water and mix with mushroom soup; pour over chips and onions. Top with cheese. Bake in preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes.